Preheat oven to 425 degrees. In a #small pot{}, bring @water{1%cup} and a large pinch of
@salt{pinch} to a boil. Place the @Half Chicken{1%unit} on lightly oiled, #rimmed baking
sheet{} and pat dry with #paper towels{}. If you do not have a rimmed baking sheet, a
#baking dish{} will do! Rub the chicken on all sides with salt, @ground black pepper{},
@coriander{1%tsp}, and @cinnamon{1%tsp}. Place in the oven for ~{30-35%minutes}, until
golden brown and juices run clear when pierced with a #knife{}.

Meanwhile, add the @Basmati Rice{1/2%cup} to the boiling water. Reduce to a simmer and
cook covered for ~{15-20%minutes}, until tender. Thinly slice the @Scallions{2%unit},
keeping the greens and whites separate. Halve, peel, and slice the @Red Onion{1%unit} into
1/2-inch wedges. Quarter the @Fresh Figs{1%unit}.

With ~{10%minutes} to go on the chicken, take it out of the oven and add the figs and
the onions to baking sheet along with @Olive Oil{1%tsp} and a pinch of
@salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{}. Place the baking sheet back in the oven until
the chicken is cooked through and the onions and figs have caramelized.

Heat @Olive Oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add the
@Green Beans{6%ounce} and cook, tossing, until tender for ~{6-7%minutes}. Season with
salt and pepper. Set aside and cover to keep warm.

Heat another @Olive Oil{1%tsp} in the same pan over medium-high heat. Add the scallion
whites to the pan and cook, tossing, for ~{2-3%minutes}, until softened. Add the
@Veggie Stock Concentrate{1%unit}, @Honey{2%tbsp}, and @water{1%cup} to the pan. Bring
to a boil and reduce until thickened, about ~{3-4%minutes}.

When the chicken is ready, remove from the oven and let rest for ~{5%minutes}.

Serve the chicken atop the rice, with the roasted onions, figs, and green beans on the
side. Pour the pan-sauce over the plate, garnish with scallion greens and enjoy!